race.comment: MADRINA (15) has gone to a new level this time in and will relish the drop in grade. No match for the classy Weeping Woman when a fading eighth over 1200m at Kembla Grange in BM78 grade. Back to her right level and the blinkers come off. Will take holding out from the draw. LADY OLENNA (17) exciting mare from an in-form yard with a good winning record. Produced good closing splits first-up from the wide gate when a gritty second over 1100m at Rosehill in this grade. Gets the right set-up with the drop in weight. Genuine top-three player. JOISELLE (11) comes to town third-up after placing in this class last April. Set to peak with the claim and adept in all conditions. No shock to see her take this out. BENGAL (20) returns with a solid fresh record after showing a ton of ability when last in work. Back without a trial and ticks a few boxes with Grima's 3kg claim. KING LARRY (5) eye catching return with the 59kg at Scone. Gets a chance with the claim from the low draw. Value contender.
